# React Web (Next.js)

## App Router layout by role

```
app/
├── (auth)/login/
├── (admin)/          # admin only
├── (director)/       # director only
├── (teacher)/        # teacher
└── (family)/         # parent + student
```

Use route groups + middleware to enforce RBAC. Redirect wrong role to login or 403 page.

## Conventions

- **Server Components** by default; `'use client'` only for interactivity
- Functional components + TypeScript; named exports for pages
- Data fetching: Server Components call API with server-side token OR use React Query on client
- Shared types from `packages/shared` or `packages/api-client`

## API client

```typescript
// ✅ Typed client from OpenAPI
import { api } from '@/lib/api-client';

const dashboard = await api.GET('/parents/dashboard/{studentId}', {
  params: { path: { studentId } },
});
```

- Auth token in httpOnly cookie (web); attach in middleware/API route
- Never store JWT in localStorage on web

## Role-specific UI

| Role | Web-only screens |
|------|------------------|
| admin | User CRUD, module toggles |
| director | Teacher assignment, PDF reports |
| teacher | Full submission grading table |
| parent/student | Dashboard, assignments (student submits) |

## Components

- Colocate: `components/{domain}/ComponentName.tsx`
- Extract hooks: `hooks/useAssignments.ts`
- Forms: React Hook Form + Zod (schemas aligned with API DTOs)

## Styling

- Tailwind CSS; consistent spacing scale
- Accessible: labels, focus states, semantic HTML
- User-facing copy in **Spanish**

## Do not

- Duplicate API types — generate from `specs/Openapi.yml`
- Allow parent role to render submit-assignment forms
- Fetch in `useEffect` what a Server Component can load directly
